      <h1>The Electoral <em>Roll</em></h1>
      <p class="deck">If you worship with us regularly, joining the electoral roll is a simple way to say: Emmanuel is my church.</p>

    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="em-intro">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="em-body">
        <p class="em-lead">The electoral roll is how we keep track of how many people think of themselves as members of Emmanuel Church.</p>
        <p>It also helps the Diocese calculate the amount of money we pay towards central church costs. To elect new members to the Parochial Church Council or the Deanery Synod, you need to be on the electoral roll.</p>
        <p>If you worship with us on a regular basis, please consider joining the Electoral Roll — we would be glad to count you among our members.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="em-aside">
        <div class="em-aside-card">
          <h4>Join the roll</h4>
          <p>Complete and return an Application for Enrolment form, available below or from the parish office.</p>
          <a href="https://parishresources.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/Form-1-Application-for-enrolment-church-electoral-roll.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="em-btn em-btn--primary" style="margin-bottom:12px">Enrolment form (PDF)</a>
          <a href="contact.html" class="em-readmore">Questions? Contact the office →</a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="em-callout">
    <div class="inner">
      <div><h3>Make Emmanuel your <em>church home</em>.</h3><p>Joining the electoral roll is quick and simple — and it lets you take a full part in the life and decisions of the parish.</p></div>
